        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(edit): preserve unrelated lines during fuzzy text matching",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #89994. Builds on the approach in #90060 (by @SebTardif) with a critical correction.\n\n### The problem\nWhen the `edit` tool uses fuzzy matching (smart quotes, dashes, trailing whitespace), it normalizes the **entire file content** before applying replacements. This silently rewrites every unrelated line that contains Unicode characters, smart quotes, em dashes, or trailing whitespace.\n\n### The fix\n- Search in fuzzy-normalized space, but apply edits to the **original** content\n- Map fuzzy match offsets back to original positions via per-line NFKC segment mapper\n- Use `Array.from` instead of string spread for Unicode surrogate-pair safety\n\n### Correction to #90060\nThe original PR's NFKC fast-path checked `nfkcLine.length === origLine.length` to skip offset mapping. This is **incorrect** — NFKC can preserve total code-unit length while shifting internal positions. Example: `ﬁ X é` → `fi X é` — both 6 code units, but X moves from offset 2 to 3.\n\nFixed by comparing string identity (`nfkcLine === origLine`) instead of length. Added regression test for this exact case.\n\n### What was adopted from #90060\n- Offset mapper architecture (5 original commits)\n- Unicode safety improvements\n- NFKC expansion, composition, and partial ligature handling\n\n### What differs\n- NFKC fast-path uses `===` identity instead of length equality (P1 fix for ClawSweeper finding)\n- Regression test for length-neutral mixed expansion/composition case\n\n**Test plan:** `pnpm test src/agents/sessions/tools/edit-diff.test.ts`",
        "branch": "fix/edit-fuzzy-v2",
